<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-078-234 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 232 721</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Seybold Report on Publishing Systems  August 23 1991 v20 n22p46(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Seybold Publications Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Large-format color printer from Oce; to be launched in September.andO;(Oce Graphics' G5242-PS PostScript printer) (The Latest Word)(product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Oce' Graphics U.S.A. Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Oce Graphics G5242-PS (Computer printer) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionLaser PrintersDesktop PublishingColor.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Oce Graphics (previously Schlumberger Graphic) is ready to launch as A3-sizecolor Adobe Postscript printer, the model G5242-PS.andP;  It will be introduced inSeptember at the Apple Expo in Paris.andM;Oce already markets an A4 model, called the G5241, based on thermal transfertechnology and offering 300-dpi resolution.andP;  The standard product is equippedwith 12 MB of RAM d 1.5 MB of ROM, and it sports LocalTalk, Centronics,RS-232C, RS-423 and SCSI communications interfaces.andP;  The Adobe interpreterincludes the 35 basic Laser-Writer typefaces.andP;  Others faces can bedownloaded.andM;The G5242 model, like the A4 one, can handle 16.7 million colors and hasPantone certification.andP;  It can print on paper or transparency materials.andP;  Themaximum material size is A3+ (297X434 mm), offering the possibility ofoutputting on A3 reels (197X420mm) with 14mm of white space.andM;The price will be attractive.andP;  In France, Oce will charge 120,000 francs($20,000 at today's rate) for the machine and one year of site maintenance,including parts.andO;</TEXT></DOC>